94 static void layoutSegmentElements(Segment* segment, int startTrack, int endTrack)
95  {
96  for (int track = startTrack; track < endTrack; ++track) {
97  if (Element* e = segment->element(track))
98  e->layout();
99  }
100  }

102 #if 0
103 //---------------------------------------------------------
104 // vUp
105 // reurns true if chord should be treated as up
106 // for purpose of setting horizontal position
107 // for most chords, this is just chord->up()
108 // but for notes on cross-staff beams, we take care to produce more consistent results
109 // since the initial guess for up() may change during layout
110 //---------------------------------------------------------
111 static bool vUp(Chord* chord)
112  {
113  if (!chord)
114  return true;
115  else if (!chord->beam() || !chord->beam()->cross()) {
116  return chord->up();
117  }
118  else {
119  // cross-staff beam: we cannot know the actual direction of this chord until the beam layout,
120  // but that's too late - it won't work to lay out as if the chord is up on pass one but then down on pass two
121  // so just assign a logical direction based on attributes that won't change
122  // so chords can be laid out consistently on both passes
123  bool up;
124  if (chord->stemDirection() != Direction::AUTO)
125  up = chord->stemDirection() == Direction::UP;
126  else if (chord->staffMove())
127  up = chord->staffMove() > 0;
128  else if (chord->track() < chord->beam()->track())
129  up = false;
130  else if (chord->track() > chord->beam()->track())
131  up = true;
132  else if (chord->measure()->hasVoices(chord->staffIdx(), chord->tick(), chord->actualTicks()))
133  up = !(chord->track() % 2);
134  else
135  up = !chord->staff()->isTop();
136  return up;
137  }
138  }
139 #endif

141 //---------------------------------------------------------
142 // layoutChords1
143 // - layout upstem and downstem chords
144 // - offset as necessary to avoid conflict
145 //---------------------------------------------------------
146 
147 void Score::layoutChords1(Segment* segment, int staffIdx)
148  {
149  const Staff* staff = Score::staff(staffIdx);
150  const int startTrack = staffIdx * VOICES;
151  const int endTrack = startTrack + VOICES;
152  const Fraction tick = segment->tick();
153 
154  if (staff->isTabStaff(tick)) {
155  layoutSegmentElements(segment, startTrack, endTrack);
156  return;
157  }
158 
159  bool crossBeamFound = false;
160  std::vector<Note*> upStemNotes;
161  std::vector<Note*> downStemNotes;
162  int upVoices = 0;
163  int downVoices = 0;
164  qreal nominalWidth = noteHeadWidth() * staff->mag(tick);
165  qreal maxUpWidth = 0.0;
166  qreal maxDownWidth = 0.0;
167  qreal maxUpMag = 0.0;
168  qreal maxDownMag = 0.0;
169 
170  // dots and hooks can affect layout of notes as well as vice versa
171  int upDots = 0;
172  int downDots = 0;
173  bool upHooks = false;
174  bool downHooks = false;
175 
176  // also check for grace notes
177  bool upGrace = false;
178  bool downGrace = false;
179 
180  for (int track = startTrack; track < endTrack; ++track) {
181  Element* e = segment->element(track);
182  if (e && e->isChord()) {
183  Chord* chord = toChord(e);
184  if (chord->beam() && chord->beam()->cross())
185  crossBeamFound = true;
186  bool hasGraceBefore = false;
187  for (Chord* c : chord->graceNotes()) {
188  if (c->isGraceBefore())
189  hasGraceBefore = true;
190  layoutChords2(c->notes(), c->up()); // layout grace note noteheads
191  layoutChords3(c->notes(), staff, 0); // layout grace note chords
192  }
193  if (chord->up()) {
194  ++upVoices;
195  upStemNotes.insert(upStemNotes.end(), chord->notes().begin(), chord->notes().end());
196  upDots = qMax(upDots, chord->dots());
197  maxUpMag = qMax(maxUpMag, chord->mag());
198  if (!upHooks)
199  upHooks = chord->hook();
200  if (hasGraceBefore)
201  upGrace = true;
202  }
203  else {
204  ++downVoices;
205  downStemNotes.insert(downStemNotes.end(), chord->notes().begin(), chord->notes().end());
206  downDots = qMax(downDots, chord->dots());
207  maxDownMag = qMax(maxDownMag, chord->mag());
208  if (!downHooks)
209  downHooks = chord->hook();
210  if (hasGraceBefore)
211  downGrace = true;
212  }
213  }
214  }
215 
216  if (upVoices + downVoices) {
217  // TODO: use track as secondary sort criteria?
218  // otherwise there might be issues with unisons between voices
219  // in some corner cases
220 
221  maxUpWidth = nominalWidth * maxUpMag;
222  maxDownWidth = nominalWidth * maxDownMag;
223 
224  // layout upstem noteheads
225  if (upVoices > 1) {
226  std::sort(upStemNotes.begin(), upStemNotes.end(),
227  [](Note* n1, const Note* n2) ->bool {return n1->line() > n2->line(); } );
228  }
229  if (upVoices) {
230  qreal hw = layoutChords2(upStemNotes, true);
231  maxUpWidth = qMax(maxUpWidth, hw);
232  }
233 
234  // layout downstem noteheads
235  if (downVoices > 1) {
236  std::sort(downStemNotes.begin(), downStemNotes.end(),
237  [](Note* n1, const Note* n2) ->bool {return n1->line() > n2->line(); } );
238  }
239  if (downVoices) {
240  qreal hw = layoutChords2(downStemNotes, false);
241  maxDownWidth = qMax(maxDownWidth, hw);
242  }
243 
244  qreal sp = staff->spatium(tick);
245  qreal upOffset = 0.0; // offset to apply to upstem chords
246  qreal downOffset = 0.0; // offset to apply to downstem chords
247  qreal dotAdjust = 0.0; // additional chord offset to account for dots
248  qreal dotAdjustThreshold = 0.0; // if it exceeds this amount
249 
250  // centering adjustments for whole note, breve, and small chords
251  qreal centerUp = 0.0; // offset to apply in order to center upstem chords
252  qreal oversizeUp = 0.0; // adjustment to oversized upstem chord needed if laid out to the right
253  qreal centerDown = 0.0; // offset to apply in order to center downstem chords
254  qreal centerAdjustUp = 0.0; // adjustment to upstem chord needed after centering donwstem chord
255  qreal centerAdjustDown = 0.0; // adjustment to downstem chord needed after centering upstem chord
256 
257  // only center chords if they differ from nominal by at least this amount
258  // this avoids unnecessary centering on differences due only to floating point roundoff
259  // it also allows for the possibility of disabling centering
260  // for notes only "slightly" larger than nominal, like half notes
261  // but this will result in them not being aligned with each other between voices
262  // unless you change to left alignment as described in the comments below
263  qreal centerThreshold = 0.01 * sp;
264 
265  // amount by which actual width exceeds nominal, adjusted for staff mag() only
266  qreal headDiff = maxUpWidth - nominalWidth;
267  // amount by which actual width exceeds nominal, adjusted for staff & chord/note mag()
268  qreal headDiff2 = maxUpWidth - nominalWidth * (maxUpMag / staff->mag(tick));
269  if (headDiff > centerThreshold) {
270  // larger than nominal
271  centerUp = headDiff * -0.5;
272  // maxUpWidth is true width, but we no longer will care about that
273  // instead, we care only about portion to right of origin
274  maxUpWidth += centerUp;
275  // to left align rather than center, delete both of the above
276  if (headDiff2 > centerThreshold) {
277  // if max notehead is wider than nominal with chord/note mag() applied
278  // then noteheads extend to left of origin
279  // because stemPosX() is based on nominal width
280  // so we need to correct for that too
281  centerUp += headDiff2;
282  oversizeUp = headDiff2;
283  }
284  }
285  else if (-headDiff > centerThreshold) {
286  // smaller than nominal
287  centerUp = -headDiff * 0.5;
288  if (headDiff2 > centerThreshold) {
289  // max notehead is wider than nominal with chord/note mag() applied
290  // perform same adjustment as above
291  centerUp += headDiff2;
292  oversizeUp = headDiff2;
293  }
294  centerAdjustDown = centerUp;
295  }
296 
297  headDiff = maxDownWidth - nominalWidth;
298  if (headDiff > centerThreshold) {
299  // larger than nominal
300  centerDown = headDiff * -0.5;
301  // to left align rather than center, change the above to
302  //centerAdjustUp = headDiff;
303  maxDownWidth = nominalWidth - centerDown;
304  }
305  else if (-headDiff > centerThreshold) {
306  // smaller than nominal
307  centerDown = -headDiff * 0.5;
308  centerAdjustUp = centerDown;
309  }
310 
311  // handle conflict between upstem and downstem chords
312 
313  if (upVoices && downVoices) {
314  Note* bottomUpNote = upStemNotes.front();
315  Note* topDownNote = downStemNotes.back();
316  int separation;
317  // TODO: handle conflicts for cross-staff notes and notes on cross-staff beams
318  // for now we simply treat these as though there is no conflict
319  if (bottomUpNote->chord()->staffMove() == topDownNote->chord()->staffMove() && !crossBeamFound)
320  separation = topDownNote->line() - bottomUpNote->line();
321  else
322  separation = 2; // no conflict
323  QVector<Note*> overlapNotes;
324  overlapNotes.reserve(8);
325 
326  if (separation == 1) {
327  // second
328  downOffset = maxUpWidth;
329  // align stems if present, leave extra room if not
330  if (topDownNote->chord()->stem() && bottomUpNote->chord()->stem())
331  downOffset -= topDownNote->chord()->stem()->lineWidth();
332  else
333  downOffset += 0.1 * sp;
334  }
335 
336  else if (separation < 1) {
337 
338  // overlap (possibly unison)
339 
340  // build list of overlapping notes
341  for (size_t i = 0, n = upStemNotes.size(); i < n; ++i) {
342  if (upStemNotes[i]->line() >= topDownNote->line() - 1)
343  overlapNotes.append(upStemNotes[i]);
344  else
345  break;
346  }
347  for (size_t i = downStemNotes.size(); i > 0; --i) { // loop most probably needs to be in this reverse order
348  if (downStemNotes[i-1]->line() <= bottomUpNote->line() + 1)
349  overlapNotes.append(downStemNotes[i-1]);
350  else
351  break;
352  }
353  std::sort(overlapNotes.begin(), overlapNotes.end(),
354  [](Note* n1, const Note* n2) ->bool {return n1->line() > n2->line(); } );
355 
356  // determine nature of overlap
357  bool shareHeads = true; // can all overlapping notes share heads?
358  bool matchPending = false; // looking for a unison match
359  bool conflictUnison = false; // unison found
360  bool conflictSecondUpHigher = false; // second found
361  bool conflictSecondDownHigher = false; // second found
362  int lastLine = 1000;
363  Note* p = overlapNotes[0];
364  for (int i = 0, count = overlapNotes.size(); i < count; ++i) {
365  Note* n = overlapNotes[i];
366  NoteHead::Type nHeadType;
367  NoteHead::Type pHeadType;
368  Chord* nchord = n->chord();
369  Chord* pchord = p->chord();
370  if (n->mirror()) {
371  if (separation < 0) {
372  // don't try to share heads if there is any mirroring
373  shareHeads = false;
374  // don't worry about conflicts involving mirrored notes
375  continue;
376  }
377  }
378  int line = n->line();
379  int d = lastLine - line;
380  switch (d) {
381  case 0:
382  // unison
383  conflictUnison = true;
384  matchPending = false;
385  nHeadType = (n->headType() == NoteHead::Type::HEAD_AUTO) ? n->chord()->durationType().headType() : n->headType();
386  pHeadType = (p->headType() == NoteHead::Type::HEAD_AUTO) ? p->chord()->durationType().headType() : p->headType();
387  // the most important rules for sharing noteheads on unisons between voices are
388  // that notes must be one same line with same tpc
389  // noteheads must be unmirrored and of same group
390  // and chords must be same size (or else sharing code won't work)
391  if (n->headGroup() != p->headGroup() || n->tpc() != p->tpc() || n->mirror() || p->mirror() || nchord->small() != pchord->small()) {
392  shareHeads = false;
393  }
394  else {
395  // noteheads are potentially shareable
396  // it is more subjective at this point
397  // current default is to require *either* of the following:
398  // 1) both chords have same number of dots, both have stems, and both noteheads are same type and are full size (automatic match)
399  // or 2) one or more of the noteheads is not of type AUTO, but is explicitly set to match the other (user-forced match)
400  // or 3) exactly one of the noteheads is invisible (user-forced match)
401  // thus user can force notes to be shared despite differing number of dots or either being stemless
402  // by setting one of the notehead types to match the other or by making one notehead invisible
403  // TODO: consider adding a style option, staff properties, or note property to control sharing
404  if ((nchord->dots() != pchord->dots() || !nchord->stem() || !pchord->stem() || nHeadType != pHeadType || n->small() || p->small()) &&
405  ((n->headType() == NoteHead::Type::HEAD_AUTO && p->headType() == NoteHead::Type::HEAD_AUTO) || nHeadType != pHeadType) &&
406  (n->visible() == p->visible())) {
407  shareHeads = false;
408  }
409  }
410  break;
411  case 1:
412  // second
413  // trust that this won't be a problem for single unison
414  if (separation < 0) {
415  if (n->chord()->up())
416  conflictSecondUpHigher = true;
417  else
418  conflictSecondDownHigher = true;
419  shareHeads = false;
420  }
421  break;
422  default:
423  // no conflict
424  if (matchPending)
425  shareHeads = false;
426  matchPending = true;
427  }
428  p = n;
429  lastLine = line;
430  }
431  if (matchPending)
432  shareHeads = false;
433 
434  // calculate offsets
435  if (shareHeads) {
436  for (int i = overlapNotes.size() - 1; i >= 1; i -= 2) {
437  Note* previousNote = overlapNotes[i-1];
438  Note* n = overlapNotes[i];
439  if (!(previousNote->chord()->isNudged() || n->chord()->isNudged())) {
440  if (previousNote->chord()->dots() == n->chord()->dots()) {
441  // hide one set dots
442  bool onLine = !(previousNote->line() & 1);
443  if (onLine) {
444  // hide dots for lower voice
445  if (previousNote->voice() & 1)
446  previousNote->setDotsHidden(true);
447  else
448  n->setDotsHidden(true);
449  }
450  else {
451  // hide dots for upper voice
452  if (!(previousNote->voice() & 1))
453  previousNote->setDotsHidden(true);
454  else
455  n->setDotsHidden(true);
456  }
457  }
458  // formerly we hid noteheads in an effort to fix playback
459  // but this doesn't work for cases where noteheads cannot be shared
460  // so better to solve the problem elsewhere
461  }
462  }
463  }
464  else if (conflictUnison && separation == 0 && (!downGrace || upGrace))
465  downOffset = maxUpWidth + 0.3 * sp;
466  else if (conflictUnison)
467  upOffset = maxDownWidth + 0.3 * sp;
468  else if (conflictSecondUpHigher)
469  upOffset = maxDownWidth + 0.2 * sp;
470  else if ((downHooks && !upHooks) && !(upDots && !downDots))
471  downOffset = maxUpWidth + 0.3 * sp;
472  else if (conflictSecondDownHigher) {
473  if (downDots && !upDots)
474  downOffset = maxUpWidth + 0.3 * sp;
475  else {
476  upOffset = maxDownWidth - 0.2 * sp;
477  if (downHooks)
478  upOffset += 0.3 * sp;
479  }
480  }
481  else {
482  // no direct conflict, so parts can overlap (downstem on left)
483  // just be sure that stems clear opposing noteheads
484  qreal clearLeft = 0.0, clearRight = 0.0;
485  if (topDownNote->chord()->stem())
486  clearLeft = topDownNote->chord()->stem()->lineWidth() + 0.3 * sp;
487  if (bottomUpNote->chord()->stem())
488  clearRight = bottomUpNote->chord()->stem()->lineWidth() + qMax(maxDownWidth - maxUpWidth, 0.0) + 0.3 * sp;
489  else
490  downDots = 0; // no need to adjust for dots in this case
491  upOffset = qMax(clearLeft, clearRight);
492  if (downHooks) {
493  // we will need more space to avoid collision with hook
494  // but we won't need as much dot adjustment
495  upOffset = qMax(upOffset, maxDownWidth + 0.1 * sp);
496  dotAdjustThreshold = maxUpWidth - 0.3 * sp;
497  }
498  // if downstem chord is small, don't center
499  // and we might not need as much dot adjustment either
500  if (centerDown > 0.0) {
501  centerDown = 0.0;
502  centerAdjustUp = 0.0;
503  dotAdjustThreshold = (upOffset - maxDownWidth) + maxUpWidth - 0.3 * sp;
504  }
505  }
506 
507  }
508 
509  // adjust for dots
510  if ((upDots && !downDots) || (downDots && !upDots)) {
511  // only one sets of dots
512  // place between chords
513  int dots;
514  qreal mag;
515  if (upDots) {
516  dots = upDots;
517  mag = maxUpMag;
518  }
519  else {
520  dots = downDots;
521  mag = maxDownMag;
522  }
523  qreal dotWidth = segment->symWidth(SymId::augmentationDot);
524  // first dot
525  dotAdjust = styleP(Sid::dotNoteDistance) + dotWidth;
526  // additional dots
527  if (dots > 1)
528  dotAdjust += styleP(Sid::dotDotDistance) * (dots - 1);
529  dotAdjust *= mag;
530  // only by amount over threshold
531  dotAdjust = qMax(dotAdjust - dotAdjustThreshold, 0.0);
532  }
533  if (separation == 1)
534  dotAdjust += 0.1 * sp;
535 
536  }
537 
538  // apply chord offsets
539  for (int track = startTrack; track < endTrack; ++track) {
540  Element* e = segment->element(track);
541  if (e && e->isChord()) {
542  Chord* chord = toChord(e);
543  if (chord->up()) {
544  if (upOffset != 0.0) {
545  chord->rxpos() += upOffset + centerAdjustUp + oversizeUp;
546  if (downDots && !upDots)
547  chord->rxpos() += dotAdjust;
548  }
549  else
550  chord->rxpos() += centerUp;
551  }
552  else {
553  if (downOffset != 0.0) {
554  chord->rxpos() += downOffset + centerAdjustDown;
555  if (upDots && !downDots)
556  chord->rxpos() += dotAdjust;
557  }
558  else
559  chord->rxpos() += centerDown;
560  }
561  }
562  }
563 
564  // layout chords
565  std::vector<Note*> notes;
566  if (upVoices)
567  notes.insert(notes.end(), upStemNotes.begin(), upStemNotes.end());
568  if (downVoices)
569  notes.insert(notes.end(), downStemNotes.begin(), downStemNotes.end());
570  if (upVoices + downVoices > 1)
571  std::sort(notes.begin(), notes.end(),
572  [](Note* n1, const Note* n2) ->bool {return n1->line() > n2->line(); } );
573  layoutChords3(notes, staff, segment);
574  }
575 
576  layoutSegmentElements(segment, startTrack, endTrack);
577  }
578 
579 //---------------------------------------------------------
580 // layoutChords2
581 // - determine which notes need mirroring
582 // - this is called once for each stem direction
583 // eg, once for voices 1&3, once for 2&4
584 // with all notes combined and sorted to resemble one chord
585 // - return maximum non-mirrored notehead width
586 //---------------------------------------------------------
587 
588 qreal Score::layoutChords2(std::vector<Note*>& notes, bool up)
589  {
590  int startIdx, endIdx, incIdx;
591  qreal maxWidth = 0.0;
592 
593  // loop in correct direction so that first encountered notehead wins conflict
594  if (up) {
595  // loop bottom up
596  startIdx = 0;
597  endIdx = int(notes.size());
598  incIdx = 1;
599  }
600  else {
601  // loop top down
602  startIdx = int(notes.size()) - 1;
603  endIdx = -1;
604  incIdx = -1;
605  }
606 
607  int ll = 1000; // line of previous notehead
608  // hack: start high so first note won't show as conflict
609  bool lvisible = false; // was last note visible?
610  bool mirror = false; // should current notehead be mirrored?
611  // value is retained and may be used on next iteration
612  // to track mirror status of previous note
613  bool isLeft = notes[startIdx]->chord()->up(); // is notehead on left?
614  int lmove = notes[startIdx]->chord()->staffMove(); // staff offset of last note (for cross-staff beaming)
615 
616  for (int idx = startIdx; idx != endIdx; idx += incIdx) {
617  Note* note = notes[idx]; // current note
618  int line = note->line(); // line of current note
619  Chord* chord = note->chord();
620  int move = chord->staffMove(); // staff offset of current note
621 
622  // there is a conflict
623  // if this is same or adjacent line as previous note (and chords are on same staff!)
624  // but no need to do anything about it if either note is invisible
625  bool conflict = (qAbs(ll - line) < 2) && (lmove == move) && note->visible() && lvisible;
626 
627  // this note is on opposite side of stem as previous note
628  // if there is a conflict
629  // or if this the first note *after* a conflict
630  if (conflict || (chord->up() != isLeft))
631  isLeft = !isLeft;
632 
633  // determine if we would need to mirror current note
634  // to get it to the correct side
635  // this would be needed to get a note to left or downstem or right of upstem
636  // whether or not we actually do this is determined later (based on user mirror property)
637  bool nmirror = (chord->up() != isLeft);
638 
639  // by default, notes and dots are not hidden
640  // this may be changed later to allow unisons to share noteheads
641  note->setHidden(false);
642  note->setDotsHidden(false);
643 
644  // be sure chord position is initialized
645  // chord may be moved to the right later
646  // if there are conflicts between voices
647  chord->rxpos() = 0.0;
648 
649  // let user mirror property override the default we calculated
650  if (note->userMirror() == MScore::DirectionH::AUTO) {
651  mirror = nmirror;
652  }
653  else {
654  mirror = note->chord()->up();
655  if (note->userMirror() == MScore::DirectionH::LEFT)
656  mirror = !mirror;
657  }
658  note->setMirror(mirror);
659 
660  // accumulate return value
661  if (!mirror)
662  maxWidth = qMax(maxWidth, note->bboxRightPos());
663 
664  // prepare for next iteration
665  lvisible = note->visible();
666  lmove = move;
667  ll = line;
668  }
669 
670  return maxWidth;
671  }
672 
673 //---------------------------------------------------------
674 // AcEl
675 //---------------------------------------------------------
676 
677 struct AcEl {
678  Note* note;
679  qreal x; // actual x position of this accidental relative to origin
680  qreal top; // top of accidental bbox relative to staff
681  qreal bottom; // bottom of accidental bbox relative to staff
682  int line; // line of note
683  int next; // index of next accidental of same pitch class (ascending list)
684  qreal width; // width of accidental
685  qreal ascent; // amount (in sp) vertical strokes extend above body
686  qreal descent; // amount (in sp) vertical strokes extend below body
687  qreal rightClear; // amount (in sp) to right of last vertical stroke above body
688  qreal leftClear; // amount (in sp) to left of last vertical stroke below body
689  };
690 
691 //---------------------------------------------------------
692 // resolveAccidentals
693 // lx = calculated position of rightmost edge of left accidental relative to origin
694 //---------------------------------------------------------
695 
696 static bool resolveAccidentals(AcEl* left, AcEl* right, qreal& lx, qreal pd, qreal sp)
697  {
698  AcEl* upper;
699  AcEl* lower;
700  if (left->line >= right->line) {
701  upper = right;
702  lower = left;
703  }
704  else {
705  upper = left;
706  lower = right;
707  }
708 
709  qreal gap = lower->top - upper->bottom;
710 
711  // no conflict at all if there is sufficient vertical gap between accidentals
712  // the arrangement of accidentals into columns assumes accidentals an octave apart *do* clear
713  if (gap >= pd || lower->line - upper->line >= 7)
714  return false;
715 
716  qreal allowableOverlap = qMax(upper->descent, lower->ascent) - pd;
717 
718  // accidentals that are "close" (small gap or even slight overlap)
719  if (qAbs(gap) <= 0.33 * sp) {
720  // acceptable with slight offset
721  // if one of the accidentals can subsume the overlap
722  // and both accidentals allow it
723  if (-gap <= allowableOverlap && qMin(upper->descent, lower->ascent) > 0.0) {
724  qreal align = qMin(left->width, right->width);
725  lx = qMin(lx, right->x + align - pd);
726  return true;
727  }
728  }
729 
730  // amount by which overlapping accidentals will be separated
731  // for example, the vertical stems of two flat signs
732  // these need more space than we would need between non-overlapping accidentals
733  qreal overlapShift = pd * 1.41;
734 
735  // accidentals with more significant overlap
736  // acceptable if one accidental can subsume overlap
737  if (left == lower && -gap <= allowableOverlap) {
738  qreal offset = qMax(left->rightClear, right->leftClear);
739  offset = qMin(offset, left->width) - overlapShift;
740  lx = qMin(lx, right->x + offset);
741  return true;
742  }
743 
744  // accidentals with even more overlap
745  // can work if both accidentals can subsume overlap
746  if (left == lower && -gap <= upper->descent + lower->ascent - pd) {
747  qreal offset = qMin(left->rightClear, right->leftClear) - overlapShift;
748  if (offset > 0.0) {
749  lx = qMin(lx, right->x + offset);
750  return true;
751  }
752  }
753 
754  // otherwise, there is real conflict
755  lx = qMin(lx, right->x - pd);
756  return true;
757  }
758 
759 //---------------------------------------------------------
760 // layoutAccidental
761 //---------------------------------------------------------
762 
763 static QPair<qreal, qreal> layoutAccidental(AcEl* me, AcEl* above, AcEl* below, qreal colOffset, QVector<Note*>& leftNotes, qreal pnd, qreal pd, qreal sp)
764  {
765  qreal lx = colOffset;
766  Accidental* acc = me->note->accidental();
767  qreal mag = acc->mag();
768  pnd *= mag;
769  pd *= mag;
770 
771  Chord* chord = me->note->chord();
772  Staff* staff = chord->staff();
773  Fraction tick = chord->tick();
774 
775  // extra space for ledger lines
776  qreal ledgerAdjust = 0.0;
777  qreal ledgerVerticalClear = 0.0;
778  bool ledgerAbove = chord->upNote()->line() <= -2;
779  bool ledgerBelow = chord->downNote()->line() >= staff->lines(tick) * 2;
780  if (ledgerAbove || ledgerBelow) {
781  // ledger lines are present
782  // check for collision with lines above & below staff
783  // note that on 1-line staff, both collisions are possible at once
784  // TODO: account for cutouts in accidental
785  qreal lds = staff->lineDistance(tick) * sp;
786  if ((ledgerAbove && me->top + lds <= pnd) || (ledgerBelow && staff->lines(tick) * lds - me->bottom <= pnd)) {
787  ledgerAdjust = -acc->score()->styleS(Sid::ledgerLineLength).val() * sp;
788  ledgerVerticalClear = acc->score()->styleS(Sid::ledgerLineWidth).val() * 0.5 * sp;
789  lx = qMin(lx, ledgerAdjust);
790  }
791  }
792 
793  // clear left notes
794  int lns = leftNotes.size();
795  for (int i = 0; i < lns; ++i) {
796  Note* ln = leftNotes[i];
797  int lnLine = ln->line();
798  qreal lnTop = (lnLine - 1) * 0.5 * sp;
799  qreal lnBottom = lnTop + sp;
800  if (me->top - lnBottom <= pnd && lnTop - me->bottom <= pnd) {
801  qreal lnLedgerAdjust = 0.0;
802  if (lnLine <= -2 || lnLine >= staff->lines(tick) * 2) {
803  // left note has a ledger line we probably need to clear horizontally as well
804  // except for accidentals that clear the last extended ledger line vertically
805  // in these cases, the accidental may tuck closer
806  Note* lastLnNote = lnLine < 0 ? leftNotes[0] : leftNotes[lns - 1];
807  int lastLnLine = lastLnNote->line();
808  qreal ledgerY = (lastLnLine / 2) * sp;
809  if (me->line < 0 && ledgerY - me->bottom < ledgerVerticalClear)
810  lnLedgerAdjust = ledgerAdjust;
811  else if (me->line > 0 && me->top - ledgerY < ledgerVerticalClear)
812  lnLedgerAdjust = ledgerAdjust;
813  }
814  // undercut note above if possible
815  if (lnBottom - me->top <= me->ascent - pnd)
816  lx = qMin(lx, ln->x() + ln->chord()->x() + lnLedgerAdjust + me->rightClear);
817  else
818  lx = qMin(lx, ln->x() + ln->chord()->x() + lnLedgerAdjust);
819  }
820  else if (lnTop > me->bottom)
821  break;
822  }
823 
824  // clear other accidentals
825  bool conflictAbove = false;
826  bool conflictBelow = false;
827 
828  if (above)
829  conflictAbove = resolveAccidentals(me, above, lx, pd, sp);
830  if (below)
831  conflictBelow = resolveAccidentals(me, below, lx, pd, sp);
832  if (conflictAbove || conflictBelow)
833  me->x = lx - acc->width() - acc->bbox().x();
834  else if (colOffset != 0.0)
835  me->x = lx - pd - acc->width() - acc->bbox().x();
836  else
837  me->x = lx - pnd - acc->width() - acc->bbox().x();
838 
839  return QPair<qreal, qreal> (me->x, me->x + me->width);
840  }
841 
842 //---------------------------------------------------------
843 // layoutChords3
844 // - calculate positions of notes, accidentals, dots
845 //---------------------------------------------------------
846 
847 void Score::layoutChords3(std::vector<Note*>& notes, const Staff* staff, Segment* segment)
848  {
849  //---------------------------------------------------
850  // layout accidentals
851  // find column for dots
852  //---------------------------------------------------
853 
854  QVector<Note*> leftNotes; // notes to left of origin
855  leftNotes.reserve(8);
856  QVector<AcEl> aclist; // accidentals
857  aclist.reserve(8);
858 
859  // track columns of octave-separated accidentals
860  int columnBottom[7] = { -1, -1, -1, -1, -1, -1, -1 };
861 
862  Fraction tick = notes.front()->chord()->segment()->tick();
863  qreal sp = staff->spatium(tick);
864  qreal stepDistance = sp * staff->lineDistance(tick) * .5;
865  int stepOffset = staff->staffType(tick)->stepOffset();
866 
867  qreal lx = 10000.0; // leftmost notehead position
868  qreal upDotPosX = 0.0;
869  qreal downDotPosX = 0.0;
870 
871  int nNotes = int(notes.size());
872  int nAcc = 0;
873  for (int i = nNotes-1; i >= 0; --i) {
874  Note* note = notes[i];
875  Accidental* ac = note->accidental();
876  if (ac && !note->fixed()) {
877  ac->layout();
878  if (!ac->visible()) {
879  ac->setPos(ac->bbox().x() - ac->width(), 0.0);
880  }
881  else {
882  AcEl acel;
883  acel.note = note;
884  int line = note->line();
885  acel.line = line;
886  acel.x = 0.0;
887  acel.top = line * 0.5 * sp + ac->bbox().top();
888  acel.bottom = line * 0.5 * sp + ac->bbox().bottom();
889  acel.width = ac->width();
890  QPointF bboxNE = ac->symBbox(ac->symbol()).topRight();
891  QPointF bboxSW = ac->symBbox(ac->symbol()).bottomLeft();
892  QPointF cutOutNE = ac->symCutOutNE(ac->symbol());
893  QPointF cutOutSW = ac->symCutOutSW(ac->symbol());
894  if (!cutOutNE.isNull()) {
895  acel.ascent = cutOutNE.y() - bboxNE.y();
896  acel.rightClear = bboxNE.x() - cutOutNE.x();
897  }
898  else {
899  acel.ascent = 0.0;
900  acel.rightClear = 0.0;
901  }
902  if (!cutOutSW.isNull()) {
903  acel.descent = bboxSW.y() - cutOutSW.y();
904  acel.leftClear = cutOutSW.x() - bboxSW.x();
905  }
906  else {
907  acel.descent = 0.0;
908  acel.leftClear = 0.0;
909  }
910  int pitchClass = (line + 700) % 7;
911  acel.next = columnBottom[pitchClass];
912  columnBottom[pitchClass] = nAcc;
913  aclist.append(acel);
914  ++nAcc;
915  }
916  }
917 
918  Chord* chord = note->chord();
919  bool _up = chord->up();
920 
921  if (chord->stemSlash())
922  chord->stemSlash()->layout();
923 
924  qreal overlapMirror;
925  Stem* stem = chord->stem();
926  if (stem)
927  overlapMirror = stem->lineWidth();
928  else if (chord->durationType().headType() == NoteHead::Type::HEAD_WHOLE)
929  overlapMirror = styleP(Sid::stemWidth) * chord->mag();
930  else
931  overlapMirror = 0.0;
932 
933  qreal x = 0.0;
934  if (note->mirror())
935  if (_up)
936  x = chord->stemPosX() - overlapMirror;
937  else
938  x = -note->headBodyWidth() + overlapMirror;
939  else if (_up)
940  x = chord->stemPosX() - note->headBodyWidth();
941 
942  qreal ny = (note->line() + stepOffset) * stepDistance;
943  if (note->rypos() != ny) {
944  note->rypos() = ny;
945  if (chord->stem()) {
946  chord->stem()->layout();
947  if (chord->hook())
948  chord->hook()->rypos() = chord->stem()->hookPos().y();
949  }
950  }
951  note->rxpos() = x;
952 
953  // find leftmost non-mirrored note to set as X origin for accidental layout
954  // a mirrored note that extends to left of segment X origin
955  // will displace accidentals only if there is conflict
956  qreal sx = x + chord->x(); // segment-relative X position of note
957  if (note->mirror() && !chord->up() && sx < 0.0)
958  leftNotes.append(note);
959  else if (sx < lx)
960  lx = sx;
961 
962  qreal xx = x + note->headBodyWidth() + chord->pos().x();
963 
964  Direction dotPosition = note->userDotPosition();
965  if (chord->dots()) {
966  if (chord->up())
967  upDotPosX = qMax(upDotPosX, xx);
968  else {
969  downDotPosX = qMax(downDotPosX, xx);
970  }
971 
972  if (dotPosition == Direction::AUTO && nNotes > 1 && note->visible() && !note->dotsHidden()) {
973  // resolve dot conflicts
974  int line = note->line();
975  Note* above = (i < nNotes - 1) ? notes[i+1] : 0;
976  if (above && (!above->visible() || above->dotsHidden()))
977  above = 0;
978  int intervalAbove = above ? line - above->line() : 1000;
979  Note* below = (i > 0) ? notes[i-1] : 0;
980  if (below && (!below->visible() || below->dotsHidden()))
981  below = 0;
982  int intervalBelow = below ? below->line() - line : 1000;
983  if ((line & 1) == 0) {
984  // line
985  if (intervalAbove == 1 && intervalBelow != 1)
986  dotPosition = Direction::DOWN;
987  else if (intervalBelow == 1 && intervalAbove != 1)
988  dotPosition = Direction::UP;
989  else if (intervalAbove == 0 && above->chord()->dots()) {
990  // unison
991  if (((above->voice() & 1) == (note->voice() & 1))) {
992  above->setDotY(Direction::UP);
993  dotPosition = Direction::DOWN;
994  }
995  }
996  }
997  else {
998  // space
999  if (intervalAbove == 0 && above->chord()->dots()) {
1000  // unison
1001  if (!(note->voice() & 1))
1002  dotPosition = Direction::UP;
1003  else {
1004  if (!(above->voice() & 1))
1005  above->setDotY(Direction::UP);
1006  else
1007  dotPosition = Direction::DOWN;
1008  }
1009  }
1010  }
1011  }
1012  }
1013  note->setDotY(dotPosition); // also removes invalid dots
1014  }
1015 
1016  // if there are no non-mirrored notes in a downstem chord,
1017  // then use the stem X position as X origin for accidental layout
1018  if (nNotes && leftNotes.size() == nNotes)
1019  lx = notes.front()->chord()->stemPosX();
1020 
1021  if (segment) {
1022  // align all dots for segment/staff
1023  // it would be possible to dots for up & down chords separately
1024  // this would require space to have been allocated previously
1025  // when calculating chord offsets
1026  segment->setDotPosX(staff->idx(), qMax(upDotPosX, downDotPosX));
1027  }
1028 
1029  if (nAcc == 0)
1030  return;
1031 
1032  QVector<int> umi;
1033  qreal pd = styleP(Sid::accidentalDistance);
1034  qreal pnd = styleP(Sid::accidentalNoteDistance);
1035  qreal colOffset = 0.0;
1036 
1037  if (nAcc >= 2 && aclist[nAcc-1].line - aclist[0].line >= 7) {
1038 
1039  // accidentals spread over an octave or more
1040  // set up columns for accidentals with octave matches
1041  // these will start at right and work to the left
1042  // unmatched accidentals will use zig zag approach (see below)
1043  // starting to the left of the octave columns
1044 
1045  int columnTop[7] = { -1, -1, -1, -1, -1, -1, -1 };
1046 
1047  // find columns of octaves
1048  for (int pc = 0; pc < 7; ++pc) {
1049  if (columnBottom[pc] == -1)
1050  continue;
1051  // calculate column height
1052  for (int j = columnBottom[pc]; j != -1; j = aclist[j].next)
1053  columnTop[pc] = j;
1054  }
1055 
1056  // compute reasonable column order
1057  // use zig zag
1058  QVector<int> column;
1059  QVector<int> unmatched;
1060  int n = nAcc - 1;
1061  for (int i = 0; i <= n; ++i, --n) {
1062  int pc = (aclist[i].line + 700) % 7;
1063  if (aclist[columnTop[pc]].line != aclist[columnBottom[pc]].line) {
1064  if (!column.contains(pc))
1065  column.append(pc);
1066  }
1067  else
1068  unmatched.append(i);
1069  if (i == n)
1070  break;
1071  pc = (aclist[n].line + 700) % 7;
1072  if (aclist[columnTop[pc]].line != aclist[columnBottom[pc]].line) {
1073  if (!column.contains(pc))
1074  column.append(pc);
1075  }
1076  else
1077  unmatched.append(n);
1078  }
1079  int nColumns = column.size();
1080  int nUnmatched = unmatched.size();
1081 
1082  // handle unmatched accidentals
1083  for (int i = 0; i < nUnmatched; ++i) {
1084  // first try to slot it into an existing column
1085  AcEl* me = &aclist[unmatched[i]];
1086  // find column
1087  bool found = false;
1088  for (int j = 0; j < nColumns; ++j) {
1089  int pc = column[j];
1090  int above = -1;
1091  int below = -1;
1092  // find slot within column
1093  for (int k = columnBottom[pc]; k != -1; k = aclist[k].next) {
1094  if (aclist[k].line < me->line) {
1095  above = k;
1096  break;
1097  }
1098  below = k;
1099  }
1100  // check to see if accidental can fit in slot
1101  qreal myPd = pd * me->note->accidental()->mag();
1102  bool conflict = false;
1103  if (above != -1 && me->top - aclist[above].bottom < myPd)
1104  conflict = true;
1105  else if (below != -1 && aclist[below].top - me->bottom < myPd)
1106  conflict = true;
1107  if (!conflict) {
1108  // insert into column
1109  found = true;
1110  me->next = above;
1111  if (above == -1)
1112  columnTop[pc] = unmatched[i];
1113  if (below != -1)
1114  aclist[below].next = unmatched[i];
1115  else
1116  columnBottom[pc] = unmatched[i];
1117  break;
1118  }
1119  }
1120  // if no slot found, then add to list of unmatched accidental indices
1121  if (!found)
1122  umi.push_back(unmatched[i]);
1123  }
1124  nAcc = umi.size();
1125  if (nAcc > 1)
1126  std::sort(umi.begin(), umi.end());
1127 
1128  bool alignLeft = score()->styleB(Sid::alignAccidentalsLeft);
1129 
1130  // through columns
1131  for (int i = 0; i < nColumns; ++i) {
1132  // column index
1133  const int pc = column[i];
1134 
1135  qreal minX = 0.0;
1136  qreal maxX = 0.0;
1137 
1138  AcEl* below = 0;
1139  // through accidentals in this column
1140  for (int j = columnBottom[pc]; j != -1; j = aclist[j].next) {
1141  QPair<qreal, qreal> x = layoutAccidental(&aclist[j], 0, below, colOffset, leftNotes, pnd, pd, sp);
1142  minX = qMin(minX, x.first);
1143  maxX = qMin(maxX, x.second);
1144  below = &aclist[j];
1145  }
1146 
1147  // align
1148  int next = -1;
1149  for (int j = columnBottom[pc]; j != -1; j = next) {
1150  AcEl* current = &aclist[j];
1151  next = current->next;
1152  if (next != -1 && current->line == aclist[next].line)
1153  continue;
1154 
1155  if (alignLeft)
1156  current->x = minX;
1157  else
1158  current->x = maxX - current->width;
1159  }
1160  colOffset = minX;
1161  }
1162  }
1163 
1164  else {
1165  for (int i = 0; i < nAcc; ++i)
1166  umi.push_back(i);
1167  }
1168 
1169  if (nAcc) {
1170  // for accidentals with no octave matches, use zig zag approach
1171  // layout right to left in pairs, (next) highest then lowest
1172 
1173  AcEl* me = &aclist[umi[0]];
1174  AcEl* above = 0;
1175  AcEl* below = 0;
1176 
1177  // layout top accidental
1178  layoutAccidental(me, above, below, colOffset, leftNotes, pnd, pd, sp);
1179 
1180  // layout bottom accidental
1181  int n = nAcc - 1;
1182  if (n > 0) {
1183  above = me;
1184  me = &aclist[umi[n]];
1185  layoutAccidental(me, above, below, colOffset, leftNotes, pnd, pd, sp);
1186  }
1187 
1188  // layout middle accidentals
1189  if (n > 1) {
1190  for (int i = 1; i < n; ++i, --n) {
1191  // next highest
1192  below = me;
1193  me = &aclist[umi[i]];
1194  layoutAccidental(me, above, below, colOffset, leftNotes, pnd, pd, sp);
1195  if (i == n - 1)
1196  break;
1197  // next lowest
1198  above = me;
1199  me = &aclist[umi[n-1]];
1200  layoutAccidental(me, above, below, colOffset, leftNotes, pnd, pd, sp);
1201  }
1202  }
1203  }
1204 
1205  for (const AcEl& e : qAsConst(aclist)) {
1206  // even though we initially calculate accidental position relative to segment
1207  // we must record pos for accidental relative to note,
1208  // since pos is always interpreted relative to parent
1209  Note* note = e.note;
1210  qreal x = e.x + lx - (note->x() + note->chord()->x());
1211  note->accidental()->setPos(x, 0);
1212  }
1213  }

1215 #define beamModeMid(a) (a == Beam::Mode::MID || a == Beam::Mode::BEGIN32 || a == Beam::Mode::BEGIN64)
1216 
1217 bool beamNoContinue(Beam::Mode mode)
1218  {
1219  return mode == Beam::Mode::END || mode == Beam::Mode::NONE || mode == Beam::Mode::INVALID;
1220  }

1222 //---------------------------------------------------------
1223 // beamGraceNotes
1224 //---------------------------------------------------------
1225 
1226 void Score::beamGraceNotes(Chord* mainNote, bool after)
1227  {
1228  ChordRest* a1 = 0; // start of (potential) beam
1229  Beam* beam = 0; // current beam
1230  Beam::Mode bm = Beam::Mode::AUTO;
1231  QVector<Chord*> graceNotes = after ? mainNote->graceNotesAfter() : mainNote->graceNotesBefore();
1232 
1233  for (ChordRest* cr : qAsConst(graceNotes)) {
1234  bm = Groups::endBeam(cr);
1235  if ((cr->durationType().type() <= TDuration::DurationType::V_QUARTER) || (bm == Beam::Mode::NONE)) {
1236  if (beam) {
1237  beam->layoutGraceNotes();
1238  beam = 0;
1239  }
1240  if (a1) {
1241  a1->removeDeleteBeam(false);
1242  a1 = 0;
1243  }
1244  cr->removeDeleteBeam(false);
1245  continue;
1246  }
1247  if (beam) {
1248  bool beamEnd = bm == Beam::Mode::BEGIN;
1249  if (!beamEnd) {
1250  cr->replaceBeam(beam);
1251  cr = 0;
1252  beamEnd = (bm == Beam::Mode::END);
1253  }
1254  if (beamEnd) {
1255  beam->layoutGraceNotes();
1256  beam = 0;
1257  }
1258  }
1259  if (!cr)
1260  continue;
1261  if (a1 == 0)
1262  a1 = cr;
1263  else {
1264  if (!beamModeMid(bm) && (bm == Beam::Mode::BEGIN)) {
1265  a1->removeDeleteBeam(false);
1266  a1 = cr;
1267  }
1268  else {
1269  beam = a1->beam();

1271  beam = new Beam(this);
1272  beam->setGenerated(true);
1273  beam->setTrack(mainNote->track());
1274  a1->replaceBeam(beam);
1275  }
1276  cr->replaceBeam(beam);
1277  a1 = 0;
1278  }
1279  }
1280  }
1281  if (beam)
1282  beam->layoutGraceNotes();
1283  else if (a1)
1284  a1->removeDeleteBeam(false);
1285  }

1325 void Score::hideEmptyStaves(System* system, bool isFirstSystem)
1326  {
1327  int staves = _staves.size();
1328  int staffIdx = 0;
1329  bool systemIsEmpty = true;
1330 
1331  for (Staff* staff : qAsConst(_staves)) {
1332  SysStaff* ss = system->staff(staffIdx);
1333 
1334  Staff::HideMode hideMode = staff->hideWhenEmpty();
1335 
1336  if (hideMode == Staff::HideMode::ALWAYS
1337  || (styleB(Sid::hideEmptyStaves)
1338  && (staves > 1)
1339  && !(isFirstSystem && styleB(Sid::dontHideStavesInFirstSystem))
1340  && hideMode != Staff::HideMode::NEVER)) {
1341  bool hideStaff = true;
1342  for (MeasureBase* m : system->measures()) {
1343  if (!m->isMeasure())
1344  continue;
1345  Measure* measure = toMeasure(m);
1346  if (!measure->isEmpty(staffIdx)) {
1347  hideStaff = false;
1348  break;
1349  }
1350  }
1351  // check if notes moved into this staff
1352  Part* part = staff->part();
1353  int n = part->nstaves();
1354  if (hideStaff && (n > 1)) {
1355  int idx = part->staves()->front()->idx();
1356  for (int i = 0; i < part->nstaves(); ++i) {
1357  int st = idx + i;
1358 
1359  for (MeasureBase* mb : system->measures()) {
1360  if (!mb->isMeasure())
1361  continue;
1362  Measure* m = toMeasure(mb);
1363  if (staff->hideWhenEmpty() == Staff::HideMode::INSTRUMENT && !m->isEmpty(st)) {
1364  hideStaff = false;
1365  break;
1366  }
1367  for (Segment* s = m->first(SegmentType::ChordRest); s; s = s->next(SegmentType::ChordRest)) {
1368  for (int voice = 0; voice < VOICES; ++voice) {
1369  ChordRest* cr = s->cr(st * VOICES + voice);
1370  if (cr == 0 || cr->isRest())
1371  continue;
1372  int staffMove = cr->staffMove();
1373  if (staffIdx == st + staffMove) {
1374  hideStaff = false;
1375  break;
1376  }
1377  }
1378  }
1379  if (!hideStaff)
1380  break;
1381  }
1382  if (!hideStaff)
1383  break;
1384  }
1385  }
1386  ss->setShow(hideStaff ? false : staff->show());
1387  if (ss->show())
1388  systemIsEmpty = false;
1389  }
1390  else if (!staff->show()) {
1391  // TODO: OK to check this first and not bother with checking if empty?
1392  ss->setShow(false);
1393  }
1394  else {
1395  systemIsEmpty = false;
1396  ss->setShow(true);
1397  }
1398 
1399  ++staffIdx;
1400  }
1401  Staff* firstVisible = nullptr;
1402  if (systemIsEmpty) {
1403  for (Staff* staff : qAsConst(_staves)) {
1404  SysStaff* ss = system->staff(staff->idx());
1405  if (staff->showIfEmpty() && !ss->show()) {
1406  ss->setShow(true);
1407  systemIsEmpty = false;
1408  }
1409  else if (!firstVisible && staff->show()) {
1410  firstVisible = staff;
1411  }
1412  }
1413  }
1414  // dont allow a complete empty system
1415  if (systemIsEmpty) {
1416  Staff* staff = firstVisible ? firstVisible : _staves.front();
1417  SysStaff* ss = system->staff(staff->idx());
1418  ss->setShow(true);
1419  }
1420  }

1422 //---------------------------------------------------------
1423 // connectTies
1424 /// Rebuild tie connections.
1425 //---------------------------------------------------------
1426 
1427 void Score::connectTies(bool silent)
1428  {
1429  int tracks = nstaves() * VOICES;
1430  Measure* m = firstMeasure();
1431  if (!m)
1432  return;
1433 
1434  SegmentType st = SegmentType::ChordRest;
1435  for (Segment* s = m->first(st); s; s = s->next1(st)) {
1436  for (int i = 0; i < tracks; ++i) {
1437  Element* e = s->element(i);
1438  if (e == 0 || !e->isChord())
1439  continue;
1440  Chord* c = toChord(e);
1441  for (Note* n : c->notes()) {
1442  // connect a tie without end note
1443  Tie* tie = n->tieFor();
1444  if (tie && !tie->endNote()) {
1445  Note* nnote;
1446  if (_mscVersion <= 114)
1447  nnote = searchTieNote114(n);
1448  else
1449  nnote = searchTieNote(n);
1450  if (nnote == 0) {
1451  if (!silent) {
1452  qDebug("next note at %d track %d for tie not found (version %d)", s->tick().ticks(), i, _mscVersion);
1453  delete tie;
1454  n->setTieFor(0);
1455  }
1456  }
1457  else {
1458  tie->setEndNote(nnote);
1459  nnote->setTieBack(tie);
1460  }
1461  }
1462  // connect a glissando without initial note (old glissando format)
1463  for (Spanner* spanner : n->spannerBack()) {
1464  if (spanner->isGlissando() && !spanner->startElement()) {
1465  Note* initialNote = Glissando::guessInitialNote(n->chord());
1466  n->removeSpannerBack(spanner);
1467  if (initialNote) {
1468  spanner->setStartElement(initialNote);
1469  spanner->setEndElement(n);
1470  spanner->setTick(initialNote->chord()->tick());
1471  spanner->setTick2(n->chord()->tick());
1472  spanner->setTrack(n->track());
1473  spanner->setTrack2(n->track());
1474  spanner->setParent(initialNote);
1475  initialNote->add(spanner);
1476  }
1477  else {
1478  delete spanner;
1479  }
1480  }
1481  }
1482  // spanner with no end element can happen during copy/paste
1483  for (Spanner* spanner : n->spannerFor()) {
1484  if (spanner->endElement() == nullptr) {
1485  n->removeSpannerFor(spanner);
1486  delete spanner;
1487  }
1488  }
1489  }
1490 #if 0 // chords are set in tremolo->layout()
1491  // connect two note tremolos
1492  Tremolo* tremolo = c->tremolo();
1493  if (tremolo && tremolo->twoNotes() && !tremolo->chord2()) {
1494  for (Segment* ls = s->next1(st); ls; ls = ls->next1(st)) {
1495  Element* element = ls->element(i);
1496  if (!element)
1497  continue;
1498  if (!element->isChord())
1499  qDebug("cannot connect tremolo");
1500  else {
1501  Chord* nc = toChord(element);
1502  nc->setTremolo(tremolo);
1503  tremolo->setChords(c, nc);
1504  // cross-measure tremolos are not supported
1505  // but can accidentally result from copy & paste
1506  // remove them now
1507  if (c->measure() != nc->measure())
1508  c->remove(tremolo);
1509  }
1510  break;
1511  }
1512  }
1513 #endif
1514  }
1515  }
1516  }

1518 //---------------------------------------------------------
1519 // checkDivider
1520 //---------------------------------------------------------
1521 
1522 static void checkDivider(bool left, System* s, qreal yOffset, bool remove = false)
1523  {
1524  SystemDivider* divider = left ? s->systemDividerLeft() : s->systemDividerRight();
1525  if ((s->score()->styleB(left ? Sid::dividerLeft : Sid::dividerRight)) && !remove) {
1526  if (!divider) {
1527  divider = new SystemDivider(s->score());
1528  divider->setDividerType(left ? SystemDivider::Type::LEFT : SystemDivider::Type::RIGHT);
1529  divider->setGenerated(true);
1530  s->add(divider);
1531  }
1532  divider->layout();
1533  divider->rypos() = divider->height() * .5 + yOffset;
1534  if (left) {
1535  divider->rypos() += s->score()->styleD(Sid::dividerLeftY) * SPATIUM20;
1536  divider->rxpos() = s->score()->styleD(Sid::dividerLeftX) * SPATIUM20;
1537  }
1538  else {
1539  divider->rypos() += s->score()->styleD(Sid::dividerRightY) * SPATIUM20;
1540  divider->rxpos() = s->score()->styleD(Sid::pagePrintableWidth) * DPI - divider->width();
1541  divider->rxpos() += s->score()->styleD(Sid::dividerRightX) * SPATIUM20;
1542  }
1543  }
1544  else if (divider) {
1545  if (divider->generated()) {
1546  s->remove(divider);
1547  delete divider;
1548  }
1549  else
1550  s->score()->undoRemoveElement(divider);
1551  }
1552  }

1555 // almostZero
1556 //---------------------------------------------------------
1557 
1558 bool inline almostZero(qreal value)
1559  {
1560  // 1e-3 is close enough to zero to see it as zero.
1561  return value > -1e-3 && value < 1e-3;
1562  }

1564 //---------------------------------------------------------
1565 // distributeStaves
1566 //---------------------------------------------------------
1567 
1568 static void distributeStaves(Page* page)
1569  {
1570  Score* score { page->score() };
1571  VerticalGapDataList vgdl;
1572 
1573  // Find and classify all gaps between staves.
1574  int ngaps { 0 };
1575  qreal prevYBottom { page->tm() };
1576  qreal yBottom { 0.0 };
1577  bool vbox { false };
1578  Spacer* activeSpacer { nullptr };
1579  bool transferNormalBracket { false };
1580  bool transferCurlyBracket { false };
1581  for (System* system : page->systems()) {
1582  if (system->vbox()) {
1583  VerticalGapData* vgd = new VerticalGapData(!ngaps++, system, nullptr, nullptr, nullptr, prevYBottom);
1584  vgd->addSpaceAroundVBox(true);
1585  prevYBottom = system->y();
1586  yBottom = system->y() + system->height();
1587  vbox = true;
1588  vgdl.append(vgd);
1589  transferNormalBracket = false;
1590  transferCurlyBracket = false;
1591  }
1592  else {
1593  bool newSystem { true };
1594  bool addSpaceAroundNormalBracket { false };
1595  bool addSpaceAroundCurlyBracket { false };
1596  int endNormalBracket { -1 };
1597  int endCurlyBracket { -1 };
1598  int staffNr { -1 };
1599  for (SysStaff* sysStaff : *system->staves()) {
1600  Staff* staff { score->staff(++staffNr)};
1601  addSpaceAroundNormalBracket |= endNormalBracket == staffNr;
1602  addSpaceAroundCurlyBracket |= endCurlyBracket == staffNr;
1603  for (const BracketItem* bi : staff->brackets()) {
1604  if (bi->bracketType() == BracketType::NORMAL) {
1605  addSpaceAroundNormalBracket |= staff->idx() > (endNormalBracket - 1);
1606  endNormalBracket = qMax(endNormalBracket, staff->idx() + bi->bracketSpan());
1607  }
1608  else if(bi->bracketType() == BracketType::BRACE) {
1609  addSpaceAroundCurlyBracket |= staff->idx() > (endCurlyBracket - 1);
1610  endCurlyBracket = qMax(endCurlyBracket, staff->idx() + bi->bracketSpan());
1611  }
1612  }
1613 
1614  if (!sysStaff->show())
1615  continue;
1616 
1617  VerticalGapData* vgd = new VerticalGapData(!ngaps++, system, staff, sysStaff, activeSpacer, prevYBottom);
1618  activeSpacer = nullptr;
1619 
1620  if (newSystem) {
1621  vgd->addSpaceBetweenSections();
1622  newSystem = false;
1623  }
1624  if (addSpaceAroundNormalBracket || transferNormalBracket) {
1625  vgd->addSpaceAroundNormalBracket();
1626  addSpaceAroundNormalBracket = false;
1627  transferNormalBracket = false;
1628  }
1629  if (addSpaceAroundCurlyBracket || transferCurlyBracket) {
1630  vgd->addSpaceAroundCurlyBracket();
1631  addSpaceAroundCurlyBracket = false;
1632  transferCurlyBracket = false;
1633  }
1634  else if (staffNr < endCurlyBracket) {
1635  vgd->insideCurlyBracket();
1636  }
1637 
1638  if (vbox) {
1639  vgd->addSpaceAroundVBox(false);
1640  vbox = false;
1641  }
1642 
1643  prevYBottom = system->y() + sysStaff->y() + sysStaff->bbox().height();
1644  yBottom = system->y() + sysStaff->y() + sysStaff->skyline().south().max();
1645  vgdl.append(vgd);
1646  }
1647  transferNormalBracket = endNormalBracket >= 0;
1648  transferCurlyBracket = endCurlyBracket >= 0;
1649  }
1650  activeSpacer = system->getActiveSpacer();
1651  }
1652  --ngaps;
1653 
1654  qreal spaceLeft { page->height() - page->bm() - score->styleP(Sid::staffLowerBorder) - yBottom };
1655  if (activeSpacer)
1656  spaceLeft -= activeSpacer->gap();
1657  if (spaceLeft <= 0.0)
1658  return;
1659 
1660  // Try to make the gaps equal, taking the spread factors and maximum spacing into account.
1661  static const int maxPasses { 20 }; // Saveguard to prevent endless loops.
1662  int pass { 0 };
1663  while (!almostZero(spaceLeft) && (ngaps > 0) && (++pass < maxPasses)) {
1664  ngaps = 0;
1665  qreal smallest { vgdl.smallest() };
1666  qreal nextSmallest { vgdl.smallest(smallest) };
1667  if (almostZero(smallest) || almostZero(nextSmallest))
1668  break;
1669 
1670  if ((nextSmallest - smallest) * vgdl.sumStretchFactor() > spaceLeft)
1671  nextSmallest = smallest + spaceLeft/vgdl.sumStretchFactor();
1672 
1673  qreal addedSpace { 0.0 };
1674  VerticalGapDataList modified;
1675  for (VerticalGapData* vgd : vgdl) {
1676  if (!almostZero(vgd->spacing() - smallest))
1677  continue;
1678  qreal step { nextSmallest - vgd->spacing() };
1679  if (step < 0.0)
1680  continue;
1681  step = vgd->addSpacing(step);
1682  if (!almostZero(step)) {
1683  addedSpace += step * vgd->factor();
1684  modified.append(vgd);
1685  ++ngaps;
1686  }
1687  if ((spaceLeft - addedSpace) <= 0.0)
1688  break;
1689  }
1690  if ((spaceLeft - addedSpace) <= 0.0)
1691  {
1692  for (VerticalGapData* vgd : modified)
1693  vgd->undoLastAddSpacing();
1694  ngaps = 0;
1695  }
1696  else {
1697  spaceLeft -= addedSpace;
1698  }
1699  }
1700 
1701  // If there is still space left, distribute the space of the staves.
1702  const qreal maxPageFill { score->styleP(Sid::maxPageFillSpread) };
1703  pass = 0;
1704  ngaps = 1;
1705  while (!almostZero(spaceLeft) && !almostZero(maxPageFill) && (ngaps > 0) && (++pass < maxPasses)) {
1706  ngaps = 0;
1707  qreal addedSpace { 0.0 };
1708  for (VerticalGapData* vgd : vgdl) {
1709  qreal step = spaceLeft / vgdl.sumStretchFactor();
1710  step = vgd->addFillSpacing(step, maxPageFill);
1711  if (!almostZero(step)) {
1712  addedSpace += step * vgd->factor();
1713  ++ngaps;
1714  }
1715  }
1716  spaceLeft -= addedSpace;
1717  }
1718 
1719  QSet<System*> systems;
1720  qreal systemShift { 0.0 };
1721  qreal staffShift { 0.0 };
1722  System* prvSystem { nullptr };
1723  for (VerticalGapData* vgd : vgdl) {
1724  if (vgd->sysStaff)
1725  systems.insert(vgd->system);
1726  systemShift += vgd->actualAddedSpace();
1727  if (prvSystem == vgd->system) {
1728  staffShift += vgd->actualAddedSpace();
1729  }
1730  else {
1731  vgd->system->rypos() += systemShift;
1732  if (prvSystem) {
1733  prvSystem->setDistance(vgd->system->y() - prvSystem->y());
1734  prvSystem->setHeight(prvSystem->height() + staffShift);
1735  }
1736  staffShift = 0.0;
1737  }
1738 
1739  if (vgd->sysStaff)
1740  vgd->sysStaff->bbox().translate(0.0, staffShift);
1741 
1742  prvSystem = vgd->system;
1743  }
1744  if (prvSystem) {
1745  prvSystem->setHeight(prvSystem->height() + staffShift);
1746  }
1747 
1748  for (System* system : systems) {
1749  system->setMeasureHeight(system->height());
1750  system->layoutBracketsVertical();
1751  system->layoutInstrumentNames();
1752  }
1753  vgdl.deleteAll();
1754  }
1755 
1756 //---------------------------------------------------------
1757 // layoutPage
1758 // restHeight - vertical space which has to be distributed
1759 // between systems
1760 // The algorithm tries to produce most equally spaced
1761 // systems.
1762 //---------------------------------------------------------
1763 
1764 static void layoutPage(Page* page, qreal restHeight)
1765  {
1766  if (restHeight < 0.0) {
1767  qDebug("restHeight < 0.0: %f\n", restHeight);
1768  restHeight = 0;
1769  }
1770 
1771  Score* score = page->score();
1772  int gaps = page->systems().size() - 1;
1773 
1774  QList<System*> sList;
1775 
1776  // build list of systems (excluding last)
1777  // set initial distance for each to the unstretched minimum distance to next
1778  for (int i = 0; i < gaps; ++i) {
1779  System* s1 = page->systems().at(i);
1780  System* s2 = page->systems().at(i+1);
1781  s1->setDistance(s2->y() - s1->y());
1782  if (s1->vbox() || s2->vbox() || s1->hasFixedDownDistance()) {
1783  if (s2->vbox()) {
1784  checkDivider(true, s1, 0.0, true); // remove
1785  checkDivider(false, s1, 0.0, true); // remove
1786  checkDivider(true, s2, 0.0, true); // remove
1787  checkDivider(false, s2, 0.0, true); // remove
1788  }
1789  continue;
1790  }
1791  sList.push_back(s1);
1792  }
1793 
1794  // last system needs no divider
1795  System* lastSystem = page->systems().back();
1796  checkDivider(true, lastSystem, 0.0, true); // remove
1797  checkDivider(false, lastSystem, 0.0, true); // remove
1798 
1799  if (sList.empty() || MScore::noVerticalStretch || score->enableVerticalSpread() || score->layoutMode() == LayoutMode::SYSTEM) {
1800  if (score->layoutMode() == LayoutMode::FLOAT) {
1801  qreal y = restHeight * .5;
1802  for (System* system : page->systems())
1803  system->move(QPointF(0.0, y));
1804  }
1805  else if ((score->layoutMode() != LayoutMode::SYSTEM) && score->enableVerticalSpread())
1806  distributeStaves(page);
1807 
1808  // system dividers
1809  for (int i = 0; i < gaps; ++i) {
1810  System* s1 = page->systems().at(i);
1811  System* s2 = page->systems().at(i+1);
1812  if (!(s1->vbox() || s2->vbox())) {
1813  qreal yOffset = s1->height() + (s1->distance()-s1->height()) * .5;
1814  checkDivider(true, s1, yOffset);
1815  checkDivider(false, s1, yOffset);
1816  }
1817  }
1818  return;
1819  }
1820 
1821  qreal maxDist = score->maxSystemDistance();
1822 
1823  // allocate space as needed to normalize system distance (bottom of one system to top of next)
1824  std::sort(sList.begin(), sList.end(), [](System* a, System* b) { return a->distance() - a->height() < b->distance() - b->height(); });
1825  System* s0 = sList[0];
1826  qreal dist = s0->distance() - s0->height(); // distance for shortest system
1827  for (int i = 1; i < sList.size(); ++i) {
1828  System* si = sList[i];
1829  qreal ndist = si->distance() - si->height(); // next taller system
1830  qreal fill = ndist - dist; // amount by which this system distance exceeds next shorter
1831  if (fill > 0.0) {
1832  qreal totalFill = fill * i; // space required to add this amount to all shorter systems
1833  if (totalFill > restHeight) {
1834  totalFill = restHeight; // too much; adjust amount
1835  fill = restHeight / i;
1836  }
1837  for (int k = 0; k < i; ++k) { // add amount to all shorter systems
1838  System* s = sList[k];
1839  qreal d = s->distance() + fill;
1840  if ((d - s->height()) > maxDist) // but don't exceed max system distance
1841  d = qMax(maxDist + s->height(), s->distance());
1842  s->setDistance(d);
1843  }
1844  restHeight -= totalFill; // reduce available space for next iteration
1845  if (restHeight <= 0)
1846  break; // no space left
1847  }
1848  dist = ndist; // set up for next iteration
1849  }
1850 
1851  if (restHeight > 0.0) { // space left?
1852  qreal fill = restHeight / sList.size();
1853  for (System* s : qAsConst(sList)) { // allocate it to systems equally
1854  qreal d = s->distance() + fill;
1855  if ((d - s->height()) > maxDist) // but don't exceed max system distance
1856  d = qMax(maxDist + s->height(), s->distance());
1857  s->setDistance(d);
1858  }
1859  }
1860 
1861  qreal y = page->systems().at(0)->y();
1862  for (int i = 0; i < gaps; ++i) {
1863  System* s1 = page->systems().at(i);
1864  System* s2 = page->systems().at(i+1);
1865  s1->rypos() = y;
1866  y += s1->distance();
1867 
1868  if (!(s1->vbox() || s2->vbox())) {
1869  qreal yOffset = s1->height() + (s1->distance()-s1->height()) * .5;
1870  checkDivider(true, s1, yOffset);
1871  checkDivider(false, s1, yOffset);
1872  }
1873  }
1874  page->systems().back()->rypos() = y;
1875  }

1893 //---------------------------------------------------------
1894 
1895 static qreal sff2(qreal width, qreal xMin, const SpringMap& springs)
1896  {
1897  if (width <= xMin)
1898  return 0.0;
1899  auto i = springs.begin();
1900  qreal c = i->second.stretch;
1901  if (c == 0.0) //DEBUG
1902  c = 1.1;
1903  qreal f = 0.0;
1904  for (; i != springs.end();) {
1905  xMin -= i->second.fix;
1906  f = (width - xMin) / c;
1907  ++i;
1908  if (i == springs.end() || f <= i->first)
1909  break;
1910  c += i->second.stretch;
1911  }
1912  return f;
1913  }
1914 
1915 //---------------------------------------------------------
1916 // respace
1917 //---------------------------------------------------------
1918 
1919 void Score::respace(std::vector<ChordRest*>* elements)
1920  {
1921  ChordRest* cr1 = elements->front();
1922  ChordRest* cr2 = elements->back();
1923  int n = int(elements->size());
1924  qreal x1 = cr1->segment()->pos().x();
1925  qreal x2 = cr2->segment()->pos().x();
1926 
1927 #if (!defined (_MSCVER) && !defined (_MSC_VER))
1928  qreal width[n-1];
1929  int ticksList[n-1];
1930 #else
1931  // MSVC does not support VLA. Replace with std::vector. If profiling determines that the
1932  // heap allocation is slow, an optimization might be used.
1933  std::vector<qreal> width(n-1);
1934  std::vector<int> ticksList(n-1);
1935 #endif
1936  int minTick = 100000;
1937 
1938  for (int i = 0; i < n-1; ++i) {
1939  ChordRest* cr = (*elements)[i];
1940  ChordRest* ncr = (*elements)[i+1];
1941  width[i] = cr->shape().minHorizontalDistance(ncr->shape());
1942  ticksList[i] = cr->ticks().ticks();
1943  minTick = qMin(ticksList[i], minTick);
1944  }
1945 
1946  //---------------------------------------------------
1947  // compute stretches
1948  //---------------------------------------------------
1949 
1950  SpringMap springs;
1951  qreal minimum = 0.0;
1952  for (int i = 0; i < n-1; ++i) {
1953  qreal w = width[i];
1954  int t = ticksList[i];
1955  qreal str = 1.0 + 0.865617 * log(qreal(t) / qreal(minTick));
1956  qreal d = w / str;
1957 
1958  springs.insert(std::pair<qreal, Spring>(d, Spring(i, str, w)));
1959  minimum += w;
1960  }
1961 
1962  //---------------------------------------------------
1963  // distribute stretch to elements
1964  //---------------------------------------------------
1965 
1966  qreal force = sff2(x2 - x1, minimum, springs);
1967  for (auto i = springs.begin(); i != springs.end(); ++i) {
1968  qreal stretch = force * i->second.stretch;
1969  if (stretch < i->second.fix)
1970  stretch = i->second.fix;
1971  width[i->second.seg] = stretch;
1972  }
1973  qreal x = x1;
1974  for (int i = 1; i < n-1; ++i) {
1975  x += width[i-1];
1976  ChordRest* cr = (*elements)[i];
1977  qreal dx = x - cr->segment()->pos().x();
1978  cr->rxpos() += dx;
1979  }
1980  }

1982 //---------------------------------------------------------
1983 // getNextPage
1984 //---------------------------------------------------------
1985 
1986 void LayoutContext::getNextPage()
1987  {
1988  if (!page || curPage >= score->npages()) {
1989  page = new Page(score);
1990  score->pages().push_back(page);
1991  prevSystem = nullptr;
1992  pageOldMeasure = nullptr;
1993  }
1994  else {
1995  page = score->pages()[curPage];
1996  QList<System*>& systems = page->systems();
1997  pageOldMeasure = systems.isEmpty() ? nullptr : systems.back()->measures().back();
1998  const int i = systems.indexOf(curSystem);
1999  if (i > 0 && systems[i-1]->page() == page) {
2000  // Current and previous systems are on the current page.
2001  // Erase only the current and the following systems
2002  // as the previous one will not participate in layout.
2003  systems.erase(systems.begin() + i, systems.end());
2004  }
2005  else // system is not on the current page (or will be the first one)
2006  systems.clear();
2007  prevSystem = systems.empty() ? nullptr : systems.back();
2008  }
2009  page->bbox().setRect(0.0, 0.0, score->loWidth(), score->loHeight());
2010  page->setNo(curPage);
2011  qreal x = 0.0;
2012  qreal y = 0.0;
2013  if (curPage) {
2014  Page* prevPage = score->pages()[curPage - 1];
2015  if (MScore::verticalOrientation())
2016  y = prevPage->pos().y() + page->height() + MScore::verticalPageGap;
2017  else {
2018  qreal gap = (curPage + score->pageNumberOffset()) & 1 ? MScore::horizontalPageGapOdd : MScore::horizontalPageGapEven;
2019  x = prevPage->pos().x() + page->width() + gap;
2020  }
2021  }
2022  ++curPage;
2023  page->setPos(x, y);
2024  }

2366 //---------------------------------------------------------

2368 // return true if this might be a measure in a
2369 // multi measure rest

2371 
2372 static bool validMMRestMeasure(Measure* m)
2373  {

2392  if (!s->element(track)->isRest())
2393  return false;
2394  restFound = true;
2395  }
2396  }
2397  for (Element* e : s->annotations()) {
2398  if (e->isFermata())
2399  return false;
2400  }
2401  if (restFound)
2402  ++n;
2403  // measure is not empty if there is more than one rest
2404  if (n > 1)

2406  }
2407  }

2411 //---------------------------------------------------------
2412 // breakMultiMeasureRest
2413 // return true if this measure should start a new
2414 // multi measure rest
2415 //---------------------------------------------------------
2416 
2417 static bool breakMultiMeasureRest(Measure* m)
2418  {
2419  if (m->breakMultiMeasureRest())
2420  return true;
2421 
2422  if (m->repeatStart()
2423  || (m->prevMeasure() && m->prevMeasure()->repeatEnd())
2424  || (m->isIrregular())
2425  || (m->prevMeasure() && m->prevMeasure()->isIrregular())
2426  || (m->prevMeasure() && (m->prevMeasure()->sectionBreak())))
2427  return true;
2428 
2429  auto sl = m->score()->spannerMap().findOverlapping(m->tick().ticks(), m->endTick().ticks());
2430  for (auto i : sl) {
2431  Spanner* s = i.value;
2432  // break for first measure of volta or textline and first measure *after* volta
2433  if ((s->isVolta() || s->isTextLine()) && (s->tick() == m->tick() || s->tick2() == m->tick()))
2434  return true;
2435  }
2436 
2437  // break for marker in this measure
2438  for (Element* e : m->el()) {
2439  if (e->isMarker()) {
2440  Marker* mark = toMarker(e);
2441  if (!(mark->align() & Align::RIGHT))
2442  return true;
2443  }
2444  }
2445 
2446  // break for marker & jump in previous measure
2447  Measure* pm = m->prevMeasure();
2448  if (pm) {
2449  for (Element* e : pm->el()) {
2450  if (e->isJump())
2451  return true;
2452  else if (e->isMarker()) {
2453  Marker* mark = toMarker(e);
2454  if (mark->align() & Align::RIGHT)
2455  return true;
2456  }
2457  }
2458  }
2459 
2460  for (Segment* s = m->first(); s; s = s->next()) {
2461  for (Element* e : s->annotations()) {
2462  if (!e->visible())
2463  continue;
2464  if (e->isRehearsalMark() ||
2465  e->isTempoText() ||
2466  ((e->isHarmony() || e->isStaffText() || e->isSystemText() || e->isInstrumentChange()) && (e->systemFlag() || m->score()->staff(e->staffIdx())->show())))
2467  return true;
2468  }
2469  for (int staffIdx = 0; staffIdx < m->score()->nstaves(); ++staffIdx) {
2470  if (!m->score()->staff(staffIdx)->show())
2471  continue;
2472  Element* e = s->element(staffIdx * VOICES);
2473  if (!e || e->generated())
2474  continue;
2475  if (s->isStartRepeatBarLineType())
2476  return true;
2477  if (s->isType(SegmentType::KeySig | SegmentType::TimeSig) && m->tick().isNotZero())
2478  return true;
2479  if (s->isClefType()) {
2480  if (s->tick() != m->endTick() && m->tick().isNotZero())
2481  return true;
2482  }
2483  }
2484  }
2485  if (pm) {
2486  Segment* s = pm->findSegmentR(SegmentType::EndBarLine, pm->ticks());
2487  if (s) {
2488  for (int staffIdx = 0; staffIdx < s->score()->nstaves(); ++staffIdx) {
2489  BarLine* bl = toBarLine(s->element(staffIdx * VOICES));
2490  if (bl) {
2491  BarLineType t = bl->barLineType();
2492  if (t != BarLineType::NORMAL && t != BarLineType::BROKEN && t != BarLineType::DOTTED && !bl->generated())
2493  return true;
2494  else
2495  break;
2496  }
2497  }
2498  }
2499  if (pm->findSegment(SegmentType::Clef, m->tick()))
2500  return true;
2501  }
2502  return false;
2503  }

2533  if (!stf->show() || (stf->isTabStaff(measure->tick()) && stf->staffType(measure->tick())->stemless()))

2542  Fraction stretch = Fraction(1,1);

2544 
2545  // if this measure is simple meter (actually X/4),
2546  // then perform a prepass to determine the subdivision of each beat
2547 
2548  beatSubdivision.clear();
2549  TimeSig* ts = stf->timeSig(measure->tick());

2551  stretch = ts ? ts->stretch() : Fraction(1,1);
2552

2556  for (Segment* s = measure->first(st); s; s = s->next(st)) {
2557  ChordRest* mcr = toChordRest(s->element(track));

2561  if (beatSubdivision.contains(beat))
2562  beatSubdivision[beat] = qMin(beatSubdivision[beat], mcr->durationType());
2563  else
2564  beatSubdivision[beat] = mcr->durationType();
2565  }
2566  }
2567

2579  if (prevCR) {

2589  }
2590  }
2591  }

2594  if (l)
2595  l->layout();
2596  }

2599  // (tied chords?)
2600  if (cr->isChord()) {

2602  beamGraceNotes(chord, false); // grace before
2603  beamGraceNotes(chord, true); // grace after
2604  // set up for cross-measure values as soon as possible
2605  // to have all computations (stems, hooks, ...) consistent with it

2608  }
2609

2612  else

2614 
2615  // perform additional context-dependent checks
2616  if (bm == Beam::Mode::AUTO) {
2617  // check if we need to break beams according to minimum duration in current / previous beat
2618  if (checkBeats && cr->rtick().isNotZero()) {

2620  // check if on the beat
2621  if ((tick.ticks() % MScore::division) == 0) {
2622  int beat = tick.ticks() / MScore::division;
2623  // get minimum duration for this & previous beat
2624  TDuration minDuration = qMin(beatSubdivision[beat], beatSubdivision[beat - 1]);
2625  // re-calculate beam as if this were the duration of current chordrest

2627  TDuration saveCMDuration = cr->crossMeasureDurationType();

2630  bm = Groups::endBeam(cr, prev);

2633  cr->setCrossMeasureDurationType(saveCMDuration);
2634  }
2635  }

2639

2642

2644  bm = Beam::Mode::NONE;
2645 
2646  if ((cr->isChord() && cr->durationType().type() <= TDuration::DurationType::V_QUARTER) || (bm == Beam::Mode::NONE)) {
2647  bool removeBeam = true;
2648  if (beam) {
2649  beam->layout1();

2651  beam = 0;
2652  }
2653  if (a1) {

2655  a1->removeDeleteBeam(false);
2656  a1 = 0;
2657  }
2658  cr->removeDeleteBeam(false);
2659  continue;
2660  }
2661 
2662  if (beam) {

2664  if (!beamEnd) {
2665  cr->replaceBeam(beam);
2666  cr = 0;
2667  beamEnd = (bm == Beam::Mode::END);
2668  }
2669  if (beamEnd) {

2672  }
2673  }
2674  if (!cr)
2675  continue;
2676 
2677  if (a1 == 0)

2679  else {

2683  || (a1->segment()->segmentType() != cr->segment()->segmentType())

2690  }
2691  else {

2697  a1->replaceBeam(beam);

2699  cr->replaceBeam(beam);
2700  a1 = 0;
2701  }
2702  }
2703  }
2704  if (beam)

2706  else if (a1) {

2709  ChordRest* nextCR = (m ? m->findChordRest(nextTick, track) : nullptr);
2710  Beam* b = a1->beam();
2711  if (!(b && b->elements().startsWith(a1) && nextCR && beamModeMid(nextCR->beamMode())))

2713  }
2714  }

2717 //---------------------------------------------------------
2718 // breakCrossMeasureBeams
2719 //---------------------------------------------------------
2720 
2721 static void breakCrossMeasureBeams(Measure* measure)
2722  {
2723  MeasureBase* mbNext = measure->next();
2724  if (!mbNext || !mbNext->isMeasure())
2725  return;
2726 
2727  Measure* next = toMeasure(mbNext);
2728  Score* score = measure->score();
2729  const int ntracks = score->ntracks();
2730  Segment* fstSeg = next->first(SegmentType::ChordRest);
2731  if (!fstSeg)
2732  return;
2733 
2734  for (int track = 0; track < ntracks; ++track) {
2735  Staff* stf = score->staff(track2staff(track));
2736 
2737  // dont compute beams for invisible staves and tablature without stems
2738  if (!stf->show() || (stf->isTabStaff(measure->tick()) && stf->staffType(measure->tick())->stemless()))
2739  continue;
2740 
2741  Element* e = fstSeg->element(track);
2742  if (!e || !e->isChordRest())
2743  continue;
2744 
2745  ChordRest* cr = toChordRest(e);
2746  Beam* beam = cr->beam();
2747  if (!beam || beam->elements().front()->measure() == next) // no beam or not cross-measure beam
2748  continue;
2749 
2750  std::vector<ChordRest*> mElements;
2751  std::vector<ChordRest*> nextElements;
2752 
2753  for (ChordRest* beamCR : beam->elements()) {
2754  if (beamCR->measure() == measure)
2755  mElements.push_back(beamCR);
2756  else
2757  nextElements.push_back(beamCR);
2758  }
2759 
2760  if (mElements.size() == 1)
2761  mElements[0]->removeDeleteBeam(false);
2762 
2763  Beam* newBeam = nullptr;
2764  if (nextElements.size() > 1) {
2765  newBeam = new Beam(score);
2766  newBeam->setGenerated(true);
2767  newBeam->setTrack(track);
2768  }
2769 
2770  const bool nextBeamed = bool(newBeam);
2771  for (ChordRest* nextCR : nextElements) {
2772  nextCR->removeDeleteBeam(nextBeamed);
2773  if (newBeam)
2774  newBeam->add(nextCR);
2775  }
2776 
2777  if (newBeam)
2778  newBeam->layout1();
2779  }
2780  }

2805 //---------------------------------------------------------
2806 // extendedStemLenWithTwoNotesTremolo
2807 // Goal: To extend stem of one of the chords to make the tremolo less steep
2808 // Returns a modified pair of stem lengths of two chords
2809 //---------------------------------------------------------
2810 
2811 std::pair<qreal, qreal> extendedStemLenWithTwoNoteTremolo(Tremolo* tremolo, qreal stemLen1, qreal stemLen2)
2812  {
2813  const qreal spatium = tremolo->spatium();
2814  Chord* c1 = tremolo->chord1();
2815  Chord* c2 = tremolo->chord2();
2816  Stem* s1 = c1->stem();
2817  Stem* s2 = c2->stem();
2818  const qreal sgn1 = c1->up() ? -1.0 : 1.0;
2819  const qreal sgn2 = c2->up() ? -1.0 : 1.0;
2820  const qreal stemTipDistance = (s1 && s2) ? (s2->pagePos().y() + stemLen2) - (s1->pagePos().y() + stemLen1)
2821  : (c2->stemPos().y() + stemLen2) - (c1->stemPos().y() + stemLen1);
2822 
2823  // same staff & same direction: extend one of the stems
2824  if (c1->staffMove() == c2->staffMove() && c1->up() == c2->up()) {
2825  const bool stem1Higher = stemTipDistance > 0.0;
2826  if (std::abs(stemTipDistance) > 1.0 * spatium) {
2827  if ((c1->up() && !stem1Higher) || (!c1->up() && stem1Higher))
2828  return { stemLen1 + sgn1 * (std::abs(stemTipDistance) - 1.0 * spatium), stemLen2 };
2829  else /* if ((c1->up() && stem1Higher) || (!c1->up() && !stem1Higher)) */
2830  return { stemLen1, stemLen2 + sgn2 * (std::abs(stemTipDistance) - 1.0 * spatium) };
2831  }
2832  }
2833 
2834 // TODO: cross-staff two-note tremolo. Currently doesn't generate the right result in some cases.
2835 #if 0
2836  // cross-staff & beam between staves: extend both stems by the same length
2837  else if (tremolo->crossStaffBeamBetween()) {
2838  const qreal sw = tremolo->score()->styleS(Sid::tremoloStrokeWidth).val();
2839  const qreal td = tremolo->score()->styleS(Sid::tremoloDistance).val();
2840  const qreal tremoloMinHeight = ((tremolo->lines() - 1) * td + sw) * spatium;
2841  const qreal dy = c1->up() ? tremoloMinHeight - stemTipDistance : tremoloMinHeight + stemTipDistance;
2842  const bool tooShort = dy > 1.0 * spatium;
2843  const bool tooLong = dy < -1.0 * spatium;
2844  const qreal idealDistance = 1.0 * spatium - tremoloMinHeight;
2845 
2846  if (tooShort)
2847  return { stemLen1 + sgn1 * (std::abs(stemTipDistance) - idealDistance) / 2.0,
2848  stemLen2 + sgn2 * (std::abs(stemTipDistance) - idealDistance) / 2.0 };
2849  else if (tooLong)
2850  return { stemLen1 - sgn1 * (std::abs(stemTipDistance) + idealDistance) / 2.0,
2851  stemLen2 - sgn2 * (std::abs(stemTipDistance) + idealDistance) / 2.0 };
2852  }
2853 #endif
2854 
2855  return { stemLen1, stemLen2 };
2856  }
