3546 //---------------------------------------------------------
3547 // alignHarmonies
3548 //---------------------------------------------------------
3549 
3550 void alignHarmonies(const System* system, const std::vector<Segment*>& sl, bool harmony, const qreal maxShiftAbove, const qreal maxShiftBelow)
3551  {
3552 
3553  // Help class.
3554  // Contains harmonies/fretboard per segment.
3555  class HarmonyList : public QList<Element*> {
3556  QMap<const Segment*, QList<Element*>> elements;
3557  QList<Element*> modified;
3558 
3559  Element* getReferenceElement(const Segment* s, bool above, bool visible) const
3560  {
3561  // Returns the reference element for aligning.
3562  // When a segments contains multiple harmonies/fretboard, the lowest placed
3563  // element (for placement above, otherwise the highest placed element) is
3564  // used for alignment.
3565  Element* element { nullptr };
3566  for (Element* e : elements[s]) {
3567  // Only chord symbols have styled offset, fretboards don't.
3568  if (!e->autoplace() || (e->isHarmony() && !e->isStyled(Pid::OFFSET)) || (visible && !e->visible()))
3569  continue;
3570  if (!element) {
3571  element = e;
3572  }
3573  else {
3574  if ((e->placeAbove() && above && (element->y() < e->y())) ||
3575  (e->placeBelow() && !above && (element->y() > e->y())))
3576  element = e;
3577  }
3578  }
3579  return element;
3580  }
3581 
3582  public:
3583  HarmonyList()
3584  {
3585  elements.clear();
3586  modified.clear();
3587  }
3588 
3589  void append(const Segment* s, Element* e)
3590  {
3591  elements[s].append(e);
3592  }
3593 
3594  qreal getReferenceHeight(bool above) const
3595  {
3596  // The reference height is the height of
3597  // the lowest element if placed above
3598  // or
3599  // the highest element if placed below.
3600  bool first { true };
3601  qreal ref { 0.0 };
3602  for (auto s : elements.keys()) {
3603  Element* e { getReferenceElement(s, above, true) };
3604  if (!e)
3605  continue;
3606  if (e->placeAbove() && above) {
3607  ref = first ? e->y() : qMin(ref, e->y());
3608  first = false;
3609  }
3610  else if (e->placeBelow() && !above) {
3611  ref = first ? e->y() : qMax(ref, e->y());
3612  first = false;
3613  }
3614  }
3615  return ref;
3616  }
3617 
3618  bool align(bool above, qreal reference, qreal maxShift)
3619  {
3620  // Align the elements. If a segment contains multiple elements,
3621  // only the reference elements is used in the algorithm. All other
3622  // elements will remain their original placement with respect to
3623  // the reference element.
3624  bool moved { false };
3625  if (almostZero(reference))
3626  return moved;
3627 
3628  for (auto s : elements.keys()) {
3629  QList<Element*> handled;
3630  Element* be = getReferenceElement(s, above, false);
3631  if (!be)
3632  // If there are only invisible elements, we have to use an invisible
3633  // element for alignment reference.
3634  be = getReferenceElement(s, above, true);
3635  if (be && ((above && (be->y() < (reference + maxShift))) || ((!above && (be->y() > (reference - maxShift)))))) {
3636  qreal shift = be->rypos();
3637  be->rypos() = reference - be->ryoffset();
3638  shift -= be->rypos();
3639  for (Element* e : elements[s]) {
3640  if ((above && e->placeBelow()) || (!above && e->placeAbove()))
3641  continue;
3642  modified.append(e);
3643  handled.append(e);
3644  moved = true;
3645  if (e != be)
3646  e->rypos() -= shift;
3647  }
3648  for (auto e : handled)
3649  elements[s].removeOne(e);
3650  }
3651  }
3652  return moved;
3653  }
3654 
3655  void addToSkyline(const System* system)
3656  {
3657  for (Element* e : qAsConst(modified)) {
3658  const Segment* s = toSegment(e->parent());
3659  const MeasureBase* m = toMeasureBase(s->parent());
3660  system->staff(e->staffIdx())->skyline().add(e->shape().translated(e->pos() + s->pos() + m->pos()));
3661  if (e->isFretDiagram()) {
3662  FretDiagram* fd = toFretDiagram(e);
3663  Harmony* h = fd->harmony();
3664  if (h)
3665  system->staff(e->staffIdx())->skyline().add(h->shape().translated(h->pos() + fd->pos() + s->pos() + m->pos()));
3666  else
3667  system->staff(e->staffIdx())->skyline().add(fd->shape().translated(fd->pos() + s->pos() + m->pos()));
3668  }
3669  }
3670  }
3671  };
3672 
3673  if (almostZero(maxShiftAbove) && almostZero(maxShiftBelow))
3674  return;
3675 
3676  // Collect all fret diagrams and chord symbol and store them per staff.
3677  // In the same pass, the maximum height is collected.
3678  QMap<int, HarmonyList> staves;
3679  for (const Segment* s : sl) {
3680  for (Element* e : s->annotations()) {
3681  if ((harmony && e->isHarmony()) || (!harmony && e->isFretDiagram()))
3682  staves[e->staffIdx()].append(s, e);
3683  }
3684  }
3685 
3686  for (int idx: staves.keys()) {
3687  // Align the objects.
3688  // Algorithm:
3689  // - Find highest placed harmony/fretdiagram.
3690  // - Align all harmony/fretdiagram objects placed between height and height-maxShiftAbove.
3691  // - Repeat for all harmony/fretdiagram objects below heigt-maxShiftAbove.
3692  bool moved { true };
3693  int pass { 0 };
3694  while (moved && (pass++ < 10)) {
3695  moved = false;
3696  moved |= staves[idx].align(true, staves[idx].getReferenceHeight(true), maxShiftAbove);
3697  moved |= staves[idx].align(false, staves[idx].getReferenceHeight(false), maxShiftBelow);
3698  }
3699 
3700  // Add all aligned objects to the sky line.
3701  staves[idx].addToSkyline(system);
3702  }
3703  }

4628 void LayoutContext::collectPage()
4629  {
4630  const qreal slb = score->styleP(Sid::staffLowerBorder);
4631  bool breakPages = score->layoutMode() != LayoutMode::SYSTEM;
4632  qreal ey = page->height() - page->bm();
4633  qreal y = 0.0;
4634 
4635  System* nextSystem = 0;
4636  int systemIdx = -1;
4637 
4638  // re-calculate positions for systems before current
4639  // (they may have been filled on previous layout)
4640  int pSystems = page->systems().size();
4641  if (pSystems > 0) {
4642  page->system(0)->restoreLayout2();
4643  y = page->system(0)->y() + page->system(0)->height();
4644  }
4645  else {
4646  y = page->tm();
4647  }
4648  for (int i = 1; i < pSystems; ++i) {
4649  System* cs = page->system(i);
4650  System* ps = page->system(i - 1);
4651  qreal distance = ps->minDistance(cs);
4652  y += distance;
4653  cs->setPos(page->lm(), y);
4654  cs->restoreLayout2();
4655  y += cs->height();
4656  }
4657 
4658  for (int k = 0;;++k) {
4659  //
4660  // calculate distance to previous system
4661  //
4662  qreal distance;
4663  if (prevSystem)
4664  distance = prevSystem->minDistance(curSystem);
4665  else {
4666  // this is the first system on page
4667  if (curSystem->vbox())
4668  distance = 0.0;
4669  else {
4670  distance = score->styleP(Sid::staffUpperBorder);
4671  bool fixedDistance = false;
4672  // TODO: curSystem->spacerDistance(true)
4673  for (MeasureBase* mb : curSystem->measures()) {
4674  if (mb->isMeasure()) {
4675  Measure* m = toMeasure(mb);
4676  Spacer* sp = m->vspacerUp(0); // TODO: first visible?
4677  if (sp) {
4678  if (sp->spacerType() == SpacerType::FIXED) {
4679  distance = sp->gap();
4680  fixedDistance = true;
4681  break;
4682  }
4683  else
4684  distance = qMax(distance, sp->gap());
4685  }
4686 //TODO::ws distance = qMax(distance, -m->staffShape(0).top());
4687  }
4688  }
4689  if (!fixedDistance)
4690  distance = qMax(distance, curSystem->minTop());
4691  }
4692  }
4693 //TODO-ws ??
4694 // distance += score->staves().front()->userDist();
4695 
4696  y += distance;
4697  curSystem->setPos(page->lm(), y);
4698  curSystem->restoreLayout2();
4699  page->appendSystem(curSystem);
4700  y += curSystem->height();
4701 
4702  //
4703  // check for page break or if next system will fit on page
4704  //
4705  bool collected = false;
4706  if (rangeDone) {
4707  // take next system unchanged
4708  if (systemIdx > 0) {
4709  nextSystem = score->systems().value(systemIdx++);
4710  if (!nextSystem) {
4711  // TODO: handle next movement
4712  }
4713  }
4714  else {
4715  nextSystem = systemList.empty() ? 0 : systemList.takeFirst();
4716  if (nextSystem)
4717  score->systems().append(nextSystem);
4718  else if (score->isMaster()) {
4719  MasterScore* ms = static_cast<MasterScore*>(score)->next();
4720  if (ms) {
4721  score = ms;
4722  systemIdx = 0;
4723  nextSystem = score->systems().value(systemIdx++);
4724  }
4725  }
4726  }
4727  }
4728  else {
4729  nextSystem = score->collectSystem(*this);
4730  if (nextSystem)
4731  collected = true;
4732  if (!nextSystem && score->isMaster()) {
4733  MasterScore* ms = static_cast<MasterScore*>(score)->next();
4734  if (ms) {
4735  score = ms;
4736  QList<System*>& systems = ms->systems();
4737  if (systems.empty() || systems.front()->measures().empty()) {
4738  systemList = systems;
4739  systems.clear();
4740  measureNo = 0;
4741  startWithLongNames = true;
4742  firstSystem = true;
4743  tick = Fraction(0,1);
4744  prevMeasure = 0;
4745  curMeasure = 0;
4746  nextMeasure = ms->measures()->first();
4747  ms->getNextMeasure(*this);
4748  nextSystem = ms->collectSystem(*this);
4749  ms->setScoreFont(ScoreFont::fontFactory(ms->styleSt(Sid::MusicalSymbolFont)));
4750  ms->setNoteHeadWidth(ms->scoreFont()->width(SymId::noteheadBlack, ms->spatium() / SPATIUM20));
4751  }
4752  else {
4753  rangeDone = true;
4754  systemIdx = 0;
4755  nextSystem = score->systems().value(systemIdx++);
4756  }
4757  }
4758  }
4759  }
4760  prevSystem = curSystem;
4761  Q_ASSERT(curSystem != nextSystem);
4762  curSystem = nextSystem;
4763 
4764  bool breakPage = !curSystem || (breakPages && prevSystem->pageBreak());
4765 
4766  if (!breakPage) {
4767  qreal dist = prevSystem->minDistance(curSystem) + curSystem->height();
4768  Box* vbox = curSystem->vbox();
4769  if (vbox) {
4770  dist += vbox->bottomGap();
4771  }
4772  else if (!prevSystem->hasFixedDownDistance()) {
4773  qreal margin = qMax(curSystem->minBottom(), curSystem->spacerDistance(false));
4774  dist += qMax(margin, slb);
4775  }
4776  breakPage = (y + dist) >= ey && breakPages;
4777  }
4778  if (breakPage) {
4779  qreal dist = qMax(prevSystem->minBottom(), prevSystem->spacerDistance(false));
4780  dist = qMax(dist, slb);
4781  layoutPage(page, ey - (y + dist));
4782  // if we collected a system we cannot fit onto this page,
4783  // we need to collect next page in order to correctly set system positions
4784  if (collected)
4785  pageOldMeasure = nullptr;
4786  break;
4787  }
4788  }
4789 
4790  Fraction stick = Fraction(-1,1);
4791  for (System* s : page->systems()) {
4792  Score* currentScore = s->score();
4793  for (MeasureBase* mb : s->measures()) {
4794  if (!mb->isMeasure())
4795  continue;
4796  Measure* m = toMeasure(mb);
4797  if (stick == Fraction(-1,1))
4798  stick = m->tick();
4799 
4800  for (int track = 0; track < currentScore->ntracks(); ++track) {
4801  for (Segment* segment = m->first(); segment; segment = segment->next()) {
4802  Element* e = segment->element(track);
4803  if (!e)
4804  continue;
4805  if (e->isChordRest()) {
4806  if (!currentScore->staff(track2staff(track))->show())
4807  continue;
4808  ChordRest* cr = toChordRest(e);
4809  if (notTopBeam(cr)) // layout cross staff beams
4810  cr->beam()->layout();
4811  if (notTopTuplet(cr)) {
4812  // fix layout of tuplets
4813  DurationElement* de = cr;
4814  while (de->tuplet() && de->tuplet()->elements().front() == de) {
4815  Tuplet* t = de->tuplet();
4816  t->layout();
4817  de = t;
4818  }
4819  }
4820 
4821  if (cr->isChord()) {
4822  Chord* c = toChord(cr);
4823  for (Chord* cc : c->graceNotes()) {
4824  if (cc->beam() && cc->beam()->elements().front() == cc)
4825  cc->beam()->layout();
4826  cc->layoutSpanners();
4827  for (Element* element : cc->el()) {
4828  if (element->isSlur())
4829  element->layout();
4830  }
4831  }
4832  c->layoutArpeggio2();
4833  c->layoutSpanners();
4834  if (c->tremolo()) {
4835  Tremolo* t = c->tremolo();
4836  Chord* c1 = t->chord1();
4837  Chord* c2 = t->chord2();
4838  if (t->twoNotes() && c1 && c2 && (c1->staffMove() || c2->staffMove()))
4839  t->layout();
4840  }
4841  }
4842  }
4843  else if (e->isBarLine())
4844  toBarLine(e)->layout2();
4845  }
4846  }
4847  m->layout2();
4848  }
4849  }
4850 
4851  if (score->systemMode()) {
4852  System* s = page->systems().last();
4853  qreal height = s ? s->pos().y() + s->height() + s->minBottom() : page->tm();
4854  page->bbox().setRect(0.0, 0.0, score->loWidth(), height + page->bm());
4855  }
4856 
4857  page->rebuildBspTree();
4858  }

5039 // layout
5040 //---------------------------------------------------------
5041 
5042 void LayoutContext::layout()
5043  {
5044  MeasureBase* lmb;
5045  do {
5046  getNextPage();
5047  collectPage();
5048 
5049  if (page && !page->systems().isEmpty())
5050  lmb = page->systems().back()->measures().back();
5051  else
5052  lmb = nullptr;
5053 
5054  // we can stop collecting pages when:
5055  // 1) we reach the end of score (curSystem is nullptr)
5056  // or
5057  // 2) we have fully processed the range and reached a point of stability:
5058  // a) we have completed layout for the range (rangeDone is true)
5059  // b) we haven't collected a system that will need to go on the next page
5060  // c) this page ends with the same measure as the previous layout
5061  // pageOldMeasure will be last measure from previous layout if range was completed on or before this page
5062  // it will be nullptr if this page was never laid out or if we collected a system for next page
5063  } while (curSystem && !(rangeDone && lmb == pageOldMeasure));
5064  // && page->system(0)->measures().back()->tick() > endTick // FIXME: perhaps the first measure was meant? Or last system?
5065 
5066  if (!curSystem) {
